  "summaries": [
    {
      "id": 857502,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "A security inconsistency was identified in the user_oidc app where group-based login restrictions were enforced in the browser OIDC flow but not in bearer token validation. This could allow users outside whitelisted groups to access the Nextcloud API with a valid bearer token.\n\nExploitation requires possession of the OAuth client_secret for the OIDC client configuration to exchange an authorization code into a bearer token, limiting practical exploitability to scenarios where an attacker has privileged access to the identity provider infrastructure.",
